{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Some antibiotics bind to the large ribosomal subunit at the peptidyl-transferase centre (PTC) or adjacent to it, in the ribosomal exit tunnel. Gram-positive bacteria have antibiotic resistance (ARE) ATP-binding cassette (ABC) proteins of the F type (ABCF) that provide them resistance to that kind of antibiotics. These proteins are also found in some Gram-negative bacteria [[cite:PUB00094459]].</p>\n<p>VmlR is a ribosomal protection protein that confers resistance to lincomycin (Lnc), the streptogramin A (SA) antibiotic virginiamycin M (VgM) and the pleuromutilin antibiotic tiamulin. It is an ABCF protein that binds to the E site of the antibiotic-stalled ribosomes inducing conformational changes in the P-site, and allows the dissociation of the antibiotic from its PTC binding site [[cite:PUB00094459], [cite:PUB00094460]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"hamap" {"MF_00846" "Ribosome protection protein VmlR [vmlR]"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Ribosome protection protein VmlR", "short" "VmlR"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 56, "taxa" 338, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 410, "sets" 0, "proteins" 410, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 241}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR043684", :literature {"PUB00094460" {"URL" nil, "issue" "36", "authors" ["Crowe-McAuliffe C" "Graf M" "Huter P" "Takada H" "Abdelshahid M" "Novacek J" "Murina V" "Atkinson GC" "Hauryliuk V" "Wilson DN."], "ISO_journal" "Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.", "DOI_URL" nil, "medline_journal" "Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A", "title" "Structural basis for antibiotic resistance mediated by the Bacillus subtilis ABCF ATPase VmlR.", "year" 2018, "raw_pages" "8978-8983", "volume" "115", "ISBN" nil